<TITLE> Under-19 cricketers draw with Sri Lanka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 8 (bdnews24.com) - The second three-dayer between Bangladesh Under-19 and Sri Lanka Under-19 ended in a drab draw at the Colts ground Monday. Bangladesh were 222 for six at the close of the final day with skipper Mahmudul Hasan 81 not out . Hosts Sri Lanka, having resumed the day on 44 for one, declared their second innings at 178 for six, setting the visitors to chase 280 runs to win the match on the final day. Earlier, Bangladesh were bundled out for 228 after bowling Sri Lanka out for 329 in the first innings. The third three-dayer between the same teams will begin on July 12. The first three-dayer also ended in a draw. 
